                    <p class="detailed-view-card-description">The Golden Temple, also known as Harmandir Sahib, is a significant Sikh Gurdwara located in Amritsar, Punjab, India. Initiated by Guru Ram Das in 1581 and completed by Guru Arjan Dev in 1604, it holds profound historical and spiritual importance for Sikhs. Renowned for its stunning architecture, the temple is built on a 67-foot square platform in the center of the sacred Amrit Sarovar (Pool of Nectar), with its marble and copper structure overlaid with gold foil, giving it its distinctive golden appearance.Some famous places to visit near Taj Mahal are</p>
