                    <p class="detailed-view-card-description">The Charminar is an iconic monument located in Hyderabad, India. Built in 1591 by Muhammad Quli Qutb Shah,it commemorates the founding of Hyderabad and the end of a plague epidemic.
                     The structure features four grand arches, each crowned by a towering minaret, giving it its name "Charminar," which means "Four Minarets." The Charminar is not only a historical symbol of Hyderabad but also a bustling center of commerce and culture,
                     particularly famous for its pearls and bangles.Some famous places to visit near Taj Mahal are</p>
